        <div class="key-challenges-retail key-challenges-legal">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="mt-40">Key challenges<br> for the legal industry</h2>
                <div class="gor-100">
                    <div class="h4">
                        <p>Today’s legal sector suffers from excessive paperwork, lack of security, transparency, and
                            slow processes, all arising from outdated methods and practices. Blockchain technology is
                            designed to create an automated, fast, accessible, and tamper-proof environment for legal
                            operations.</p>
                        <p>OpenLedger offers blockchain solutions covering the following critical aspects of the legal
                            industry:</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="point-list point-list-accordion">
                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Manual work</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Legal contracts are still handwritten and certified with physical signatures, which
                                    requires time to process and the physical presence of parties. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Intellectual property</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Every day the industry faces intellectual property violation issues regarding music,
                                    videos, or works of art. Typically, violations stem from the lack of access
                                    permission control. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Data storage</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    With piles of legal documents claiming property ownership, rental, and other rights,
                                    law firms recognize the necessity of adequately organized, searchable database as
                                    never before. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Documentary evidence</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Some jurisdictions require an auditable, provable chain of custody as well as
                                    requirements for traditional documentary evidence. As a result, such documents might
                                    become not relevant at the time of their presentation. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Notary services</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Currently, legal documents, such as leases or rental agreements, require the
                                    presence of a general notary who verifies the signatures. The notarization process
                                    itself is costly and time-consuming. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Arbitration cases</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    The average turnaround for an arbitration case through FINRA is 14 months; the
                                    agency currently runs a 4,800-case backlog. Arbitration remains preferable to court
                                    proceedings but is still a slow and unwieldy process. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

