        <div class="retail-apps legal-apps">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="mt-40">Blockchain for legal: applications</h2>
                <div class="gor-100">
                    <div class="h4">
                        Blockchain has an answer to every burning question faced by the legal industry. Below are some
                        cases proving blockchain’s versatility. </div>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="row row tiles-lable enhance-tiles-lable blockchain-logistics-lable blockchain-legal-lable tiles-lable-collapse">

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                Automated contracts </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                Delegate the task of contract signing to on-chain, self-executing ‘smart’ contracts that
                                execute agreements between parties automatically when pre-arranged conditions are met.
                            </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                Tamper-proof database </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                Blockchain might serve you as a useful tool for arranging an irreversible data storage
                                where users can send FOIA requests without the risk of altering data or accessing
                                confidential information. </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                Cost-effective arbitration </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                With smart contracts, you can limit the number of cases in which disputes are possible.
                                When differences take place, smart contracts could automatically assign arbiters from
                                the selected databases. </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                Evidence tracking </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                Blockchain takes care of chain of custody recording. Evidence can be stored directly
                                on-chain, or smart contracts can require changes in custody be recorded on-chain,
                                resulting in a tamper-proof, auditable record. </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                No middlemen </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                Forget about notary services – every document on the blockchain is “marked” by a digital
                                signature serving as a proof of its validity. </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <div class="tile tile-collapse">
                            <h3>
                                Property protection </h3>
                            <div class="text">
                                Users can register intellectual property rights with unique IDs, minimizing chances for
                                violation and fraud. </div>
                            <div class="fade-out"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
